    {
      "_id": "MPParagraphElement:F9A941B2-F52E-4F0E-A022-D0E1A39E3B83",
      "contents": "<p xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" id=\"MPParagraphElement:F9A941B2-F52E-4F0E-A022-D0E1A39E3B83\" class=\"MPElement\" data-object-type=\"MPParagraphElement\">This study had several limitations. Firstly, due to limited resources, it was very difficult for us to recruit a large sample of suicide attempters with chronic schizophrenia, which may cause the bias of our findings in the statistical analysis. Hence, our findings need to be replicated in a larger and matched sample. Secondly, only a functional single nucleotide (<i>DβH</i> 5'-Ins/Del) polymorphism was tested. Further studies will investigate other <i>DβH</i> functional polymorphisms and haplotypes whether all of which were involved in cognitive regulation, and were associated with suicide attempts in chronic schizophrenia. Finally, although we performed quality controls, genotype misclassification was still possible. These factors related to cognitive performance and suicide behavior in chronic schizophrenia should be considered in future studies.</p>",
